summary: When we decided to write about that topic for "MIC Drop". I brought up all my anger and frustration pent up inside. But it...
caption: When we decided to write about that topic for “MIC Drop”. I brought up all my anger and frustration pent up inside. But it wasn’t cool at all. It felt like me when I did “No More Dream”. Even to me, I think my face, look or eyes are different from me when I did “No More Dream”. Back then, I tried to look fierce. In fact, I wasn’t fierce. You can’t become fierce by frowning. You can’t be strong if you threat others. But I did. This doesn’t make you a strong one. […] “I should not lose”. I thought like that. That made me feel hard and nervous. I had a lot of weak points. And it was not easy to fix my errors.

summary: Song of the Day - February 20, 2019 V (BTS) - Scenery [C] I love when V releases a solo track, his voice is so deep and I love...
caption:
Song of the Day - February 20, 2019

V (BTS) - Scenery

[C] I love when V releases a solo track, his voice is so deep and I love it. When I was first learning the members my first thought was that V was a rapper just because of his deep voice because usually the one with the deep voice is the rapper in the group but I was pleasantly surprised. Now I can’t get enough of this boys voice and need more of him in my life. I hope one day he releases a solo album.

[S] When V does songs like this I am always reminded of just how deep V’s voice really is and when I compare it to his face it low key weirds me out. XD Scenery is such a relaxing song I can see myself listening to this track on a bad insomnia night the way he sings the song is just so soothing and relaxing it is the perfect song to fall asleep too, 

that being said it is a song that is WAY WAY to slow for me to listen to at any point during the day except for when I am going to sleep. This song does not fit any mood for me except a sleepy one. XD

[M] V has such a deep and soothing voice. I love listening to his solo tracks for his voice and just listening to the beginning, I have a feeling that this will be one of my favourite solo tracks, if not my favourite solo track to date. This song has a fairy tale feeling and one with a happy ending and I can find myself getting lost in a moment with this song. Was this song released as an OST track because it would make the best song for a romantic drama moment! I can’t wait until V decides to release a solo album, it’s only a matter of time.

- Johnnys Jr group Snowman having new members
- Arashi’s hiatus announcement

I also have to mention that I’ve been following BTS from a distance for a few years and do enjoy their music so there’s no shade here.
